02/09/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- The foreign ministry accused Turkey on Tuesday (September 1st) of flying aircraft over the Aegean Sea, which separates the two countries, and violating its airspace. "These ongoing violations ... are dangerous and may lead to incidents," Foreign Ministry spokesman Grigoris Delavekouras said. Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis had a telephone conversation with her Turkish counterpart Ahmet Davutoglu to express her concern. Athens plans to file a complaint with the International Civil Aviation Organisation, the EU and NATO. (Eleftherotypia - 02/09/09; AFP - 01/09/09)
